Saudi Bounced Checks Drop 60% by End of June, al-Eqtisadiah Says

-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 
2011-08-15T05:53:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-15/saudi-bounced-checks-drop-60-by-end-of-june-al-eqtisadiah-says.html
  Saudi Arabia  reported a 60 percent
decline in the amounts written on bounced checks by the end of
the second quarter,  al-Eqtisadiah  reported, citing  Saudi Credit
Bureau  General Manager Nabil Al-Mubarak.  The amount slumped to 1.1 billion riyals ($298 million) as
of June 30, from 2.78 billion riyals a year earlier, the
newspaper said. The number of bounced checks fell to 13,280 from
29,750 a year earlier, the newspaper added.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mourad Haroutunian in Riyadh at 
 mharoutunian@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net  